    link(rel='stylesheet', href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700,900', type='text/css')
  body
    header.hero(role='banner')
      .container
        h1
          .spinner-hero
          span.hero-h1-textcontent Spinners
          
        h2 A Sass mixin to generate pure CSS3 loading/busy indicators
        p.center Uses a single rotating element and a partial border. Fully customizable. <br>Use with pure Sass or Compass.

        ul.sources-list
          li
            a.sources-link(href='https://github.com/franzheidl/spinners') Spinners on Github
          li
            a.sources-link(href='https://rubygems.org/gems/spinners') Spinners on Rubygems.org
      
    section.section
      .container
        h2 Installing Spinners
        
        section.section
          h3 Download
          
          p The easiest way to use Spinners is to just clone the repo from <a href='https://github.com/franzheidl/spinners'>github</a> or download the <a href='https://github.com/franzheidl/spinners/releases'>latest release tarball</a>. The only file you'll need is <code>stylesheets/_spinners.scss</code>. Place this in the appropriate <code>sass</code> folder of your project.
        
        section.section
          h3 Install via Bower
          p To install Spinners as a Bower component run:
          
          pre
            code $ bower install spinners
        
        section.section
          h3 Compass Extension Ruby Gem
          p To install Spinners as a Compass extension run:
          
          pre
            code $ gem install spinners
            
          p and require it in your <code>config.rb</code> file:
          
          pre
            code require 'spinners'
        
    section.section
      .container
        h2 Getting Started
        
        p First, import Spinner into your main .scss file or -module:
        
        pre
          code @import "spinners";
            
        p Then declare a selector of your choice and call the mixin:
        
        pre
          code
            |.my-spinner {
            |   @include spinner();
            |}
            
        p In your html, you can use any markup element you want, a <code>div</code>, <code>span</code>, <code>i</code>, or what have you.

        p Spinners come set to <code>display: inline-block</code> and <code>vertical-align: middle</code> by default so you can put it inside buttons, alerts and the like and have it aligned. If this doesn't work for you, declare your overrides <strong>after</strong> calling the mixin:
        
        pre
          code
            | .my-spinner {
            |   @include spinner();
            |   vertical-align: top;
            |   margin-right: .5em;
            | }
        
        
    section.section
      .container
        h2 Customizing Spinners
        
        p Size, border-width, -style, -color, and the speed of the animation can be customized.
        
        section.section
          h3 Adjusting Size
        
          p By default, Spinners are set to be <code>1em</code> wide and high, so a spinner will size proportionally to its context. To customize its size, you may use any valid dimensional unit such as <code>px</code>, <code>em</code>, or <code>rem</code>:
          
          pre
            code
              | .my-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(1.25em);
              | }
        
        section.section
          h3 Adjusting border-width, -style, and -thickness
          
          p For adjusting the border, you may use any valid shorthand css border declaration or individual <code>border-{property} {value}</code> (no colon!) pairs:
          
          pre
            code
              | .my-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(3px solid #ccc);
              | }
              |   &nbsp;
              | .my-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(border-width 3px, border-style solid);
              | }
        
        section.section
          h3 Adjusting Animation Speed
          
          p To customize a spinner's animation speed, pass the number of seconds for one full rotation:
          
          pre
            code
              | .my-spinner {
              |     @include spinner(.6s);
              | }
          
          p All arguments are optional. When using mulitple customizations, pass your arguments comma-separated:
          
          pre
            code
              | .my-spinner {
              |     @include spinner(28px, 3px solid #555, .7s);
              | }
          
          p In case of invalid arguments compilation will not fail, but Spinners will output a warning and use its defaults.
        
    section.section
      .container
        h2 Examples
        
        .example
          .example-spinner
            .my-spinner-default
            | Default Spinner
            
          pre
            code
              | .my-spinner {
              |   @include spinner();
              | }
              
        .example
          .example-spinner
            .my-big-fat-spinner
            | Big Fat Spinner
            
          pre
            code
              | .my-big-fat-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(1.5em, border-width 12px);
              | }
        
        section.section
          .example-spinner
            .my-orange-dotted-spinner
            | Orange Dotted Spinner
          
          pre
            code
              | .my-orange-dotted-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(2em, 6px dotted orange);
              | }
              
        section.section
          .example-spinner
            .my-dashed-spinner
            | Dashed Spinner
            
          pre
            code
              | .my-dashed-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(1.2em, border-style dashed);
              | }
              
        section.section
          .example-spinner
            .my-double-spinner
            | Double Spinner
            
          pre
            code
              | .my-double-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(6px double fuchsia);
              | }
              
        section.section
          .example-spinner
            .my-fast-spinner
            | Fast Spinner
            
          pre
            code
              | .my-fast-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(.3s, border-width 4px, border-color #aaa);
              | }
        
        section.section
          .example-spinner
            .my-slow-spinner
            | Slow Spinner
          pre
            code
              | .my-slow-spinner {
              |   @include spinner(4s);
              | }
            
                    
    section.section
      .container
        h2 Compatibility
        
        p Works in any modern browser and IE 10+. Spinners does not come with a fallback for IE < 10, so if you need one, roll your own!
    
    
